    <div class="col-md-8">
        <p>
            Hello, and thanks for taking the time to read about me. I am a United State Navy submarine veteran who has transitioned into a career in software engineering. I very much enjoy learning about new technologies and helping others learn, as well. I’ve attained an Associate’s Degree in Technical Studies, and Bachelor’s Degrees in both Computer Engineering and Electrical Engineering. I very much enjoy writing code, and especially working with .NET technologies. I’m currently working as a software engineer for a small engineering firm that works in the transportation industry and volunteer as the Hampton Roads Chapter Leader of Operation Code. I’m a tattoo enthusiast and have been working developing a business around a Tattoo Community Application called Tattwho. This project has driven me to learn more about entrepreneurship and participating in a mastermind group at Old Dominion Innovation Center where we collectively help people develop business models for their entrepreneurial ideas.
        </p>
