<div class="row">
    <h6>Entrepreneurship</h6>
    <div class="col-md-9">
        <p>
            After school, I began working on a personal project called Tattwho using ASP.NET MVC 5 and various other technologies as a means to get better at software development. This served as my learning ground to try out various software design patterns and .NET libraries. This project helped me to grow rather quickly and become versed in domain driven design and Azure technologies. I was able to develop an MVP and get 100 users to try out the application getting very positive feedback. This opened my eyes to the power of knowledge in software engineering. Software developers have the ability to turn an idea into a business with very little monetary risk. This has driven my entrepreneurial spirit and appreciation for relating business concepts to software development.
        </p>
