    <div class="col-md-6">
        <p>
            In late 2016, I began to feel the urge to recover the feeling of comradery that was left behind after the military. I started to search for local resources for teaching veterans to code. I found Operation Code and it seemed like the perfect organization for me to volunteer mentorship to veterans who wanted to learn software development. After helping a handful of veterans with mock interviews and resume building, I sought out to get a local chapter started. I got the support of a couple of venues and began having hosting monthly meetups to train veterans software development skills. Operation Code has been a great outlet for me to learn, teach, and help the military and Hampton Roads community.
